sap.me.CalendarLegend.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new CalendarLegend. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getLegendForType00 legendForType00} : string
    • {@link #getLegendForType01 legendForType01} : string
    • {@link #getLegendForType04 legendForType04} : string
    • {@link #getLegendForType06 legendForType06} : string
    • {@link #getLegendForType07 legendForType07} : string
    • {@link #getLegendForToday legendForToday} : string
    • {@link #getLegendForSelected legendForSelected} : string
    • {@link #getLegendForSelected00 legendForSelected00} : string
    • {@link #getLegendForNormal legendForNormal} : string
    • {@link #getExpandable expandable} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getExpanded expanded} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getWidth width} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize (default: auto)
    • {@link #getLegendWidth legendWidth} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize (default: 12.5rem)
    • {@link #getVisible visible} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getDesign design} : sap.me.CalendarDesign (default: Approval)
  • Aggregations
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

    • {@link #getExpandable expandable} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getExpanded expanded} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getVisible visible} : boolean (default: true)
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getContentInfo contentInfo} : sap.ui.core.Control

    • {@link #getShowOverlapIndicator showOverlapIndicator} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getVisible visible} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getSwipeToNavigate swipeToNavigate} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getWidth width} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize (default: 100%)
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getCalendarEvents calendarEvents} : sap.me.OverlapCalendarEvent[]
  • Events
    • {@link #event:endOfData endOfData} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:changeDate changeDate} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

sap.me.Calendar.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new Calendar. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getVisible visible} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getHideNavControls hideNavControls} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getHideMonthTitles hideMonthTitles} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getMonthsPerRow monthsPerRow} : int (default: 1)
    • {@link #getDayWidth dayWidth} : int (default: 45)
    • {@link #getDayHeight dayHeight} : int (default: 50)
    • {@link #getWeeksPerRow weeksPerRow} : int (default: 1)
    • {@link #getSingleRow singleRow} : boolean
    • {@link #getMonthsToDisplay monthsToDisplay} : int (default: 1)
    • {@link #getCurrentDate currentDate} : string
    • {@link #getEnableMultiselection enableMultiselection} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getFirstDayOffset firstDayOffset} : int (default: 0)
    • {@link #getDisabledWeekDays disabledWeekDays} : any
    • {@link #getDisabledDates disabledDates} : any
    • {@link #getSwipeToNavigate swipeToNavigate} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getDesign design} : sap.me.CalendarDesign (default: Approval)
    • {@link #getSelectionMode selectionMode} : sap.me.CalendarSelectionMode (default: SINGLE)
    • {@link #getWidth width} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize (default: 100%)
    • {@link #getDays days} : any
    • {@link #getMonths months} : any
  • Events
    • {@link #event:tapOnDate tapOnDate} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:changeCurrentDate changeCurrentDate} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:changeRange changeRange} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

dragDropConfig.helpDescription: Defines the drag-and-drop configuration. Note: This configuration might be ignored due to control {@link sap.ui.core.Element.extend metadata} restrictions.

models.description: A map of model instances to which the object should be attached. The models are keyed by their model name. For the default model, String(undefined) is expected.

objectBindings.description: A map of model instances to which the object should be attached. The models are keyed by their model name. For the default model, String(undefined) is expected.

busyIndicatorSize.description: The size of the BusyIndicator. For controls with a width smaller 3rem a sap.ui.core.BusyIndicatorSize.Small should be used. If the size could vary in width and the width could get smaller than 3rem, the sap.ui.core.BusyIndicatorSize.Auto option could be used. The default is set to sap.ui.core.BusyIndicatorSize.Medium For a full screen BusyIndicator use sap.ui.core.BusyIndicatorSize.Large.
busyIndicatorSize.helpDescription: The size of the BusyIndicator. For controls with a width smaller 3rem a sap.ui.core.BusyIndicatorSize.Small should be used. barColor.description: The color of the bar. Enumeration sap.ui.core.BarColor provides CRITICAL (yellow), NEGATIVE (red), POSITIVE (green), NEUTRAL (blue) (default value).
barColor.helpDescription: The color of the bar. Enumeration sap.ui.core.BarColor provides CRITICAL (yellow), NEGATIVE (red), POSITIVE (green), NEUTRAL (blue) (default value).

enabled.helpDescription: Switches enabled state of the control. Disabled fields have different colors, and cannot be focused.

fieldGroupIds.description: The IDs of a logical field group that this control belongs to. All fields in a logical field group should share the same fieldGroupId. Once a logical field group is left, the validateFieldGroup event is fired. For backward compatibility with older releases, field group IDs are syntactically not limited, but it is suggested to use only valid {@link sap.ui.core.ID}s. See {@link #attachValidateFieldGroup} or consult the {@link topic:5b0775397e394b1fb973fa207554003e Field Group} documentation.

id.description: Unique ID of this instance. If not given, a so called autoID will be generated by the framework. AutoIDs use a unique prefix that must not be used for Ids that the application (or other code) creates. It can be configured option 'autoIDPrefix', see {@link sap.ui.core.Configuration}.

validateFieldGroup.name: validateFieldGroup
validateFieldGroup.description: Event is fired if a logical field group defined by fieldGroupIds of a control was left or when the user explicitly pressed the key combination that triggers validation. By default, the RETURN key without any modifier keys triggers validation, see {@link #triggerValidateFieldGroup}. Listen to this event to validate data of the controls belonging to a field group. See {@link #setFieldGroupIds}, or consult the {@link topic:5b0775397e394b1fb973fa207554003e Field Group} documentation.
